===Etymology===
{{etyl|enm}} {{term|thin|thin, thinne|lang=enm}} from {{etyl|ang}} {{term|þynne|lang=ang}}, from {{proto|Germanic|þunnuz||þunniaz|thin|lang=en}}, (compare {{proto|Germanic|þanjanan|to stretch, spread out|lang=en}}), from {{proto|Indo-European|ténh₂us|thin|lang=la}}, from {{proto|Indo-European|tenw(ə)-|to pull, stretch}}.

===Adjective===
{{en-adj|thinner|thinnest}}

# Slim, [[narrow]] in size, and (''of a person or animal'') usually carrying little fat.
# Of low [[viscosity]] or low specific [[gravity]], e.g., as is water compared to honey.
# [[scarce|Scarce]].
# Overly [[strict]].
# {{sports}} Describing a poorly played [[golf]] shot where the ball is struck by the bottom part of the club head. See [[fat]], [[shank]], [[toe]].

